name: Sucheen Sundaram
about:
🎓 Fourth-Year Statistics Student with Data Science Minor at Cal Poly San Luis Obispo

🔍 Seeking Opportunities in Data Science and Data Engineering

💡 Passionate about Diversity, Equity, and Inclusion

📈 Harnessing Data-Driven Techniques to Foster Diversity, Equity, and Inclusion

As a dedicated final year statistics student minoring in data science at Cal Poly San Luis Obispo, I have a strong foundation in statistical analysis, data modeling, and programming. I am actively seeking opportunities in the field of data science and data engineering to apply my skills and contribute to meaningful projects.

Beyond technical expertise, I am deeply passionate about diversity, equity, and inclusion. I firmly believe that leveraging the power of data-driven techniques can create positive change and foster a more inclusive society. By analyzing data patterns, identifying biases, and developing innovative solutions, I aim to contribute to producing fair and unbiased systems.

name: Isabel Vargas
about:
Cal Poly SLO Class of 2026 | Poway High School Class of 2022

Materials Engineering Major

CPSWE | Prototype Vehicle Laboratory (PROVE) | FIRST Alumnus

As pursuing my education as a Materials Engineering major at California Polytechnic State University, I am a positive and motivated engineer with taking as many opportunities I can. Currently I am figuring out what I would pursue in industry so I wish to try out different industries and learn about everything I can to do that. My passion is manufacturing but my goal is explore other opportunities to learn different topics that I wouldn't have learned if I stick in the one I'm comfortable with.

I am proud to be a Latina in engineering and my roots where I've started from robotics. My goal is to be a role model that I wish I had when I was younger. So since I have been in high school, within my SWENext club, I have been involved in growing the STEM community to show that everyone is welcomed into this field.
